<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9672860589528></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9672860589528><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9672860589528>RE: Charm as Taunt</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9672860589528#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 26th 6:34 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.67]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>An added bonus comes in the new patch, twisting and typing can be bothersome at best. With the new hotkey 'cast #' you can type in on a hot key something in the manner of 'CHARMING MOB' on one line and 'Cast #' where the # is the slot the spell takes in your spell slots. Cast 1 being the first slot on the top. Take it from a bard that smokes and twists, it can be helpful.&nbsp;&nbsp;:)<br><br>Luen Wyrmsong 35th Bard The Rathe<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
