<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96683653431069></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96683653431069><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96683653431069>RE: Charm as Taunt</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96683653431069#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 1:42 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with you Kraxus :o)&nbsp;&nbsp;Charm is the "uber" taunt and I use to tell the casters in my group, that once a mob locks on them, they should yell, and I would charm it. But it is necessary to point out, that it takes a few seconds to target the mob (if you fight multiple mobs) and successfully charm it - there are occasionally resists that will delay the charm...  :o(   <br><br>I also like to charm a mob and to share the damage. Often I team with a warrior and when he comes back with a pull, he takes all the damage during the fight and therefore we have more downtime (cause I need more time to heal him). So I usually charm the mob once the warrior has pulled it and take about 1 bub of damage - then the warrior has dealt so much damage that he is going to take the beating from there on. If necessary I will recharm during the fight to take more smacks from the target. Using this technique a lvl 52 warrior and me have been able to kill a LDC without to much sweat (we were both at 2 bubbles of health). <br><br>The time a charm lasts is anywhere from 1 second to about 15 seconds and equipping a lute should reduce resists (for me it does) and also enhances the duration of the charm (sometimes).<br><br>Another use for charm is when you have to make a run for the border&#8230; just hit charm -cause like all bard songs it works even when you walk/run- and probably you will successfully charm your target and have one less beating on you/your group on your way out.<br><br>Sgrobi Lutebasher<br>Bard of 48 strings, E&#8217;ci<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
